(1) Spiritual Punishment3 the loss of the friendship of God, and of the internal satisfaction thence arising.

(2) Eternal Punishment3 eternal misery in the world to come.

(3) Temporal Punishment3 confined to the present life, and to external things, which does not necessarily take away either the sense of God’s grace, or the hope of eternal life. This is mainly of four kinds3 Death, Exile, Loss of Goods, Imprisonment, Ezr. vii. 26.
